column5: Well I hit another bucket list lake in the northeast area of central Ontario on Saturday in the poring rain!! Wind and cold !!! Perfect weather for chasing down brown fish (aka) smallies well they didn't disappoint !!!! Got tons in the 2lb range with several in the 3-4 range too !!! Got fish on cranks spinnerbaits & senkos as well as jerk baits !!!! Anyways here is a few .... Fish-on
Some nice fish there,and you braved the elements.wtg!!!!!!!
Nice smallies, sure are fun to catch!
It's like fall smallie action in August.  Nice chunkers.
Holy chunky munkies!  Nice fishâ€¦.looks chilly.
